04/03/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The president of the European Commission, Romano Prodi, met Albanian Integration Minister Sokol Nako on Monday (3 March) as part of a series of talks on the endorsement of the Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA). Prodi praised the government's achievements in the integration process and expressed confidence talks would advance soon. He noted that the success of reforms would be a key factor in accession talks, insisting that the completion of SAA talks remains on the EU agenda, despite the focus on other issues, such as Iraq. (ATA - 03/03/03)
